-- 
UBS Chief Executive Gruebel Is Asked to Leave, Bilan Reports

-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 
2011-09-20T12:36:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/ubs-chief-executive-gruebel-is-asked-to-leave-bilan-reports.html
UBS AG (UBSN)  Chief Executive Officer
 Oswald Gruebel  was asked to leave,  Bilan  magazine reported,
citing an unidentified person close to the bank’s board of
directors.  Geneva-based Bilan didn’t give any details on how it
obtained the information and didn’t say who asked Gruebel to
leave. Discussions at board level are under way concerning
Gruebel’s successor, the magazine said in a pre-release of a
story to be published in tomorrow’s edition.  A UBS spokesman declined to comment, Bilan said.  A spokesman for the Zurich-based bank declined to comment
when contacted by Bloomberg News, saying he hadn’t read the
Bilan story. He wouldn’t comment further.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at   gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net ;
